NAME
       reboot - reboot the machine

SYNOPSIS
       reboot [OPTION]

DESCRIPTION
       reboot instructs the system to restart.

OPTIONS
       -f, --force
              force immediate reboot; do not call shutdown

       -w, --wtmp-only
              don't actually reboot; only write wtmp record (no-op)

       -d, --no-wtmp
              don't write wtmp record

       -n, --no-sync
              don't sync before reboot

       --no-wall
              don't send wall message before rebooting

       --help display this help and exit

NOTES
       halt, reboot, and poweroff are the same binary.  The command name
       (argv[0]) determines the action:

       halt      halts the system
       reboot    reboots the system
       poweroff  powers off the system

       The -f flag skips the graceful shutdown sequence.

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       halt(1), poweroff(1), shutdown(1)

